OL,3,C'Woeful budgeting' in Home Office
OL,4,Ccausing overspends on asylum
OL,6,FBetween 2021/22 and 2023/24, plans put
OL,7,Fbefore Parliament by the Home Office
OL,8,Fat the start of each year budgeted an
OL,9,Faverage of #110 million for asylum
OL,10,Foperations, but it ended up spending
OL,11,Fmuch more ` an average of #2.6 billion
OL,12,Fper year.
OL,14,FThe IFS report claims that the "woeful
OL,15,Fway" the Home Office and HM Treasury
OL,16,Fhave budgeted for asylum costs lies at
OL,17,Fthe heart of the recent disagreement
OL,18,Fbetween Chancellor Rachel Reeves and
OL,19,Fher predecessor Jeremy Hunt.
