OL,3,C'Woeful budgeting' in Home Office
OL,4,Ccausing overspends on asylum
OL,6,FIn a financial audit of public
OL,7,Fspending conducted not long after Ms
OL,8,FReeves took office, spending pressures
OL,9,Frelating to asylum and illegal
OL,10,Fmigration were one of the largest
OL,11,Fitems identified amounting to an
OL,12,Festimated #6.4 billion in 2024/25.
OL,14,FIn response, Mr Hunt argued that this
OL,15,Fcontradicted the budgets signed off by
OL,16,Fcivil servants and presented to
OL,17,Fparliament just weeks before.
