OL,3,C'Woeful budgeting' in Home Office
OL,4,Ccausing overspends on asylum
OL,6,F"The fact that the Home Office has
OL,7,Fspent #7.6 billion more than initially
OL,8,Fbudgeted on asylum, border, visa and
OL,9,Fpassport operations over the past
OL,10,Fthree years is testament to that.
OL,12,F"When there is a one-off unexpected
OL,13,Fspike in costs or demand, spending
OL,14,Fmore than was budgeted is entirely
OL,15,Funderstandable.
OL,17,F"But when it is happening year after
OL,18,Fyear, something is going wrong with
OL,19,Fthe budgeting process. It would be far
OL,20,Fmore sensible to recognise the likely
OL,21,Famount of asylum spending up front.
