OL,6,FIt has submitted plans for 2024`25
OL,7,Fwhich already include a #1.5 billion
OL,8,Ftop-up from the Treasury, but which
OL,9,Fare nonetheless judged "not sufficient
OL,10,Fto support those currently in the
OL,11,Fasylum system".
OL,13,FEven with the #800 million of expected
OL,14,Fsavings from the new government's
OL,15,Fending of the Rwanda scheme, the
OL,16,Ffiscal watchdog is warning another top-
OL,17,Fup in the region of #4 billion
OL,18,F"appears all but inevitable".
